  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nCast\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (2335dea 2024-01-19T00:18:45.919964404Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nanvil && cast logs --subscribe '0x8c5be1e5ebec7d5bd14f71427d1e84f3dd0314c0f7b2291e5b200ac8c7c3b925'\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nStarting an anvil RPC (doesn't matter if you use a fork or not) and running `cast logs '0x8c5be1e5ebec7d5bd14f71427d1e84f3dd0314c0f7b2291e5b200ac8c7c3b925'` works just fine.\r\n\r\nHowever,\r\n```bash\r\ncast logs --subscribe '0x8c5be1e5ebec7d5bd14f71427d1e84f3dd0314c0f7b2291e5b200ac8c7c3b925'\r\n```\r\nfails with `(code: -32601, message: Method not found, data: None)`\r\n\r\nAccording to __anvil__ docs, it does support the `eth_subscribe` RPC call and is accepting websocket connections so I'm puzzled how it cannot subscribe to topics?",
